BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
OHIO:
WHEREAS, Cardinal Robert Francis Prevost was elected as the 4
267th Pope, in a continuous line back to Peter, on May 8, 2025, 5
becoming the first American Pope, and chose Leo XIV as his papal 6
name; and 7
WHEREAS, The first pontiff from the Augustinian order and 8
the first from the United States and North America, a son of the 9
Midwest, Pope Leo XIV was born in Chicago, Illinois, on 10
September 14, 1955, to Mildred Martínez and Louis Marius 11
Prevost; he grew up with two brothers, Louis Martín and John 12
Joseph; educated at the Minor Seminary of the Augustinian 13
Fathers, he went on to complete his bachelor's degree in 14
mathematics at Villanova University, where he also studied 15
philosophy; in 1977, he entered the novitiate of the Order of 16
St. Augustine in the Province of Our Mother of Good Counsel of 17

